  "id": "algorithm_001",
  "name": "Three_Crows_Three_Soldiers_Trader",
  "description": "This algorithm identifies the 'Three Black Crows' pattern for short entries and the 'Three White Soldiers' pattern for long entries on the 1-hour timeframe. It utilizes a 20-period Exponential Moving Average to confirm trends, ensuring trades align with the overall market direction.",
  "algorithm_type": "CandleStickPattern",
  "prompt": "Design an intermediate-level TechnicalPattern trading algorithm that exploits the \"Three Black Crows\" candlestick pattern for short entries and \"Three White Soldiers\" for long entries, on the 1-hour timeframe. Signal a short trade when three consecutive large bearish (close near low) candles appear after an uptrend confirmed by a 20-period Exponential Moving Average (price above EMA20 before the pattern), with stop loss at the high of the pattern and take profit at 2 times the average true range (ATR14) below entry. Signal a long trade on the reverse: three consecutive large bullish (close near high) candles after a downtrend confirmed by price below EMA20, with stop loss at the pattern low and take profit at 2 ATR14 above entry. No pyramiding; exit if price closes back above/below the EMA20 in the opposite direction. Do not use any other indicators.",
